name: "epithet"
version: "%%VERSION%%"
origin: "security/epithet"
comment: "SSH certificate authority with short-lived certificates"
maintainer: "brianm@apache.org"
www: "https://github.com/epithet-ssh/epithet"
abi: "%%ABI%%"
prefix: "/usr/local"
licenselogic: "single"
licenses: ["Apache-2.0"]
categories: ["security"]
desc: <<EOD
Epithet is an SSH certificate authority that replaces traditional SSH
key-based authentication with short-lived certificates (2-10 minutes).
It provides CA, policy, and combined server modes in a single binary,
with OIDC-based authentication and per-connection SSH agents.
EOD
